{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17639243","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17639243"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:05:28+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:05:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17769"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17769","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17769"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.88,0.04,0.04,0,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10483"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76326"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10483","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10483"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17769"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61835"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"295"},{"type":"tags","id":"1540"},{"type":"tags","id":"1713"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"10623"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24466"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24469"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76326","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76326"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a six-week history of amenorrhoea, lower abdominal pain, and abnormal vaginal bleeding. She has a history of pelvic inflammatory disease and does not take any regular medications. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. A pelvic examination reveals cervical motion tenderness. Serum beta-human chorionic gonadotropin (bHCG) levels are elevated but lower than expected for a normal intrauterine pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Ectopic pregnancy","Molar pregnancy","Threatened miscarriage","Normal intrauterine pregnancy","Ovarian cyst rupture"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with symptoms and laboratory findings suggestive of an \u003Cstrong\u003Eectopic pregnancy\u003C/strong\u003E. The history of pelvic inflammatory disease increases the risk of ectopic pregnancy due to potential tubal damage. The combination of amenorrhoea, lower abdominal pain, abnormal vaginal bleeding, and lower-than-expected serum bHCG levels is characteristic of an ectopic pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Emolar pregnancy\u003C/strong\u003E presents with significantly elevated bHCG levels and may include symptoms such as hyperemesis and uterine size larger than expected for gestational age.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Ethreatened miscarriage\u003C/strong\u003E could present with vaginal bleeding and abdominal pain, but the bHCG levels would be consistent with the gestational age unless the pregnancy is non-viable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Enormal intrauterine pregnancy\u003C/strong\u003E would not present with the combination of symptoms and lower-than-expected bHCG levels seen in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAn \u003Cstrong\u003Eovarian cyst rupture\u003C/strong\u003E could cause abdominal pain and bleeding, but it would not explain the elevated bHCG levels.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ectopic pregnancy should be suspected in women with a history of pelvic inflammatory disease presenting with amenorrhoea, abnormal vaginal bleeding and lower abdominal pain.","Serum beta-human chorionic gonadotropin (bHCG) levels in ectopic pregnancy are often lower than expected for gestational age.","Early diagnosis and management of ectopic pregnancies are crucial to prevent complications such as tubal rupture."],"references":["Hendriks E, Rosenberg R, Prine L. Ectopic Pregnancy: Diagnosis and Management. Am Fam Physician. 2020 May 15;101(10):599-606. PMID: 32412215.","Sivalingam VN, Duncan WC, Kirk E, Shephard LA, Horne AW. Diagnosis and management of ectopic pregnancy. J Fam Plann Reprod Health Care. 2011 Oct;37(4):231-40. doi: 10.1136/jfprhc-2011-0073. Epub 2011 Jul 4. PMID: 21727242; PMCID: PMC3213855.","Mullany K, Minneci M, Monjazeb R, C Coiado O. Overview of ectopic pregnancy diagnosis, management, and innovation. Womens Health (Lond). 2023 Jan-Dec;19:17455057231160349. doi: 10.1177/17455057231160349. PMID: 36999281; PMCID: PMC10071153."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61835"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17769"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61835","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61835"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-03T07:54:33+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T09:40:10+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10483"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76326"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"em